<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><rss version="2.0"><channel><title>Conteúdo de fisl13 marcado com a tag "guest speaker"</title><link>http://softwarelivre.org/fisl13</link><description>Conteúdo de fisl13 marcado com a tag "guest speaker"</description><item><title>More guest speakers confirming their presence at fisl13!</title><description>&lt;p&gt;These are the most recent confirmations. See the complete list &lt;a href="/fisl13/convidados"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Amir Taak&lt;/strong&gt; is a game developer and became known by the Bitcoin Project.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Kristian Lyngstøl&lt;/strong&gt; works at Varnish Development since 2008, with web applications since 2000 and websites since 1995.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Alberto Azevedo&lt;/strong&gt; is a corporate networks security specialist. He was general director of Nova Era Informática e Telemática and creator of the ESP-h security methodology. Hacktivist and Free Software enthusiast, he is the leader of the Project Security Experts Team and speaker in international events. He´s already spoken on fisl, with the famous "Yes, I´m a pirate, and you?"&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Aurélio Heckert&lt;/strong&gt; is a developer, digital graphics expert and Free Software advocate. he is also a Noosfero team member - that´s the platform running &lt;a href="/softwarelivre.org"&gt;softwarelivre.org&lt;/a&gt;. Co-founder and colaborator of PSL-BA, TWikiBrasil and COLIVRE.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Seth Schoen&lt;/strong&gt; works for 10 years at &lt;a href="https://www.eff.org/" target="_blank"&gt;Electronic Frontier Foundation&lt;/a&gt; , and currently he is part of the senior tech team. In these 10 years, he has contributed to improve the public uinderstanding of technology and their implications in the civil liberties. Prior to EFF, Seth helped create the live mini-distro &lt;a href="http://www.lnx-bbc.com/" target="_blank"&gt;LNX-BBC&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Felix Paul Kühne&lt;/strong&gt; is a programmer and medicine student. he worked in development of the popular VLC player for OSX (Mac) in the last 9 years. In 2010 he became the leader developer for this platform.&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 22 May 2012 13:04:56 +0000</pubDate><link>http://softwarelivre.org/fisl13/noticias/more-guest-speakers-confirming-their-presence-at-fisl13</link><guid>http://softwarelivre.org/fisl13/noticias/more-guest-speakers-confirming-their-presence-at-fisl13</guid></item><item><title>Guest speakers</title><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;The guest's list is growing every minute. See who's going to be sharing knowledge in the 13th fisl edition.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;img src="/articles/0044/8555/harvey-james-anderson.png" alt=""&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: 'Liberation Sans', Arial, sans-serif; text-align: justify; text-decoration: underline; color: #008000;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://twitter.com/#!/chefhja" style="color: #888a85; font-weight: normal; text-decoration: underline;"&gt;Harvey James Anderson&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: 'Liberation Sans', Arial, sans-serif; text-align: justify; color: #008000;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: 'Liberation Sans', Arial, sans-serif; text-align: justify;"&gt;(USA) - &lt;/span&gt;Vi&lt;/span&gt;ce President of Business Affairs and General Counsel at Mozilla. In this role, Harvey leads the business affairs, policy and legal teams. Harvey joined Mozilla in 2008 as the organization’s first in-house counsel. Harvey has counseled Internet, technology, and software clients in complex commercial transactions, as well as financial, corporate, litigation, and intellectual property matters for the past 20 years.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="font-size: 12px;"&gt; &lt;img src="/articles/0044/8533/maria.png" alt=""&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="font-size: 12px;"&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #008000;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.linkedin.com/pub/maria-bonnefon/0/3b0/823"&gt;Maria Bonnefon&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt; – &lt;span style="font-family: arial, sans-serif; color: #222222;"&gt;joined the Canonical team in 2006. She has worked in various roles including Strategic Alliance Manager for Intel and OEM Partnership Manager where she was responsible for establishing the OEM Programme. She has actively contributed to establishing alliances with major OEMs including Dell, Lenovo and Asus, as well as establishing partnerships local OEMs in EMEA, APAC, Latin America and PRC regions. She now leads the Market Development and Channel teams worldwide. She is an international business development expert with over 20 years experience both in the hardware and software fields. She has worked for various multi-national companies including Archos, Iomega and Mandriva. She holds an MBA from Georgia State University, a Masters in International Management from Ecole Supérieure de Commerce de Toulouse and a Bachelor in International Business from Auburn University. Venezuelan born, Maria is based in Bordeaux, France where she has lived for the past 14 years.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="font-size: 12px;"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="font-size: 12px;"&gt;&lt;img src="/articles/0044/8534/296646531-640.png" alt=""&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="font-size: 12px;"&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #008000;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="http://twitter.com/kylemacdonald"&gt;Kyle MacDonald&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt; – &lt;span style="font-family: arial, sans-serif; color: #222222;"&gt;Vice President of Cloud for Canonical where he is responsible for marketing, sales, business development, and product engineering for Cloud within Canonical as well as leadership in the OpenStack ecosystem. Previously, he was a founding executive at Cloud.com (acquired by Citrix in 2011) serving as its Chief Evangelist &amp;amp; Vice President of corporate development. Prior to joining Cloud.com, Kyle was Vice President of Corporate Development &amp;amp; Strategy at Wachovia Capital Partners (acquiring Hosting.com). Prior to Wachovia, he held executive leadership positions at Sun Microsystems, acquired by Oracle in 2009, leading the Web 2.0, Internet, Cloud and Next Generation Service Providers organization. Before Sun Microsystems, Kyle was Corporate Technologist for Software &amp;amp; Strategic Technology at AMD leading strategy focused on building software ecosystems and strategic alliances around 64-bit, virtualization and multi-core technology. Before AMD, Kyle was a senior engineer for Topspin Communications developing Infiniband HPC technology (acquired by Cisco in 2005). Kyle MacDonald also founded Flare Networks and served as Executive Vice President &amp;amp; CTO from it’s founding in 1998 until its acquisition in 2003. Kyle studied Sociology and Economics at Colorado State University in Fort Collins, CO.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="/articles/0044/6607/foto-fisl.png" alt=""&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #008000;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="http://twitter.com/#%21/gustavold"&gt;Gustavo Luiz Duarte&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt; (Brazil) - Developer in Linux environments for a decade now, has already contributed for various free software projects. Currently working at IBM Linux Technology Center as a mantainer of the Fedora distro for the POWER architecture.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="/articles/0044/8166/hellekin-240.png" alt=""&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hellekin (Cyberspace)&lt;/strong&gt; – Nomadic raver, interstitial resistor, infinitesimal shifter, peripheral vision, etc., Hellekin got hooked to the Internet via  IRC, *nix and GNU/Linux about 20 years ago. Since then he's been  exploring ways to emancipate himself and others using free software  exclusively. He joined the Lorea project in 2009 in Amsterdam and  has been acquainted with the Dyne Foundation, the Hackerspaces  community, and then 15M/Occupy/Globalsquare movements. He's part of  the SocialSwarm and an avid supporter of PSYC/Secushare. He  currently resides in his sleeping bag that follows him across the world. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="/articles/0044/6246/ramonramonsanchez.png" alt=""&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color: #008000;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="http://ramonramon.org/blog"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #008000;"&gt;Ramón Ramón&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt; (Espanha) – Profissional de TIC conhecido no âmbito do Conhecimento Livre na Espanha e América Latina. É Gerente de Desenvolvimento de Negocio para a América Latina na “Ándago Ingeniería”, Especialista em Software Livre e Administrações Públicas, Consultor Internacional em Tecnologias da Informação, ex-Vicepresidente da Hispalinux e fundador da Iniciativa Focus. É assessor de diversos projetos e países, como o Plano Diretor de TIC do Governo do Paraguai e o “Clúster Productivo especializado en Tecnologías Libres y Abiertas de Entre Ríos”, promovido pelo Ministério de Ciência, Tecnologia e Inovação Produtiva da Argentina. É conhecedor do desenvolvimento do Governo Aberto na Espanha e do Software Livre a nível internacional. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="/articles/0044/6254/dscn2379sb.png" alt=""&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color: #008000;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="http://twitter.com/#%21/DeirdreS"&gt;Deirdré Straughan&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000;"&gt;(Estados Unidos) - É&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; uma inovadora nas tecnologias da comunicação, indo da escrita técnica ao UI design. Ela é especialista nos novos usos da mídia, produzindo, nos anos recentes, centenas de vídeos técnicos para a Sun Microsystems, Oracle e Joyent, incluindo streams de vídeos ao vivo. Trabalha atualmente para a Joyent como Community Architect para a SmartOS e illumos open souce communities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="/articles/0044/5670/terceiro.png" alt=""&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #44aa00;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Antonio Terceiro&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt; - Desenvolvedor de software livre. Colabora com vários projetos, mas especialmente com os projetos Debian, Noosfero e Foswiki. Doutor em Ciência da Computação pela Universidade Federal da Bahia. Sócio fundador e desenvolvedor na &lt;a href="http://colivre.coop.br/" target="_blank"&gt;Colivre&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;img src="/articles/0044/2264/20050404-hansmi.png" alt=""&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #44aa00;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.google.com/url?sa=t&amp;amp;rct=j&amp;amp;q=&amp;amp;esrc=s&amp;amp;source=web&amp;amp;cd=1&amp;amp;ved=0CFcQFjAA&amp;amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fhansmi.ch%2F&amp;amp;ei=vlzXT8m1K4Gk8AS72aHnAw&amp;amp;usg=AFQjCNG9Pay-MCZEXV2bj387XcZIl4HTzA&amp;amp;sig2=e6KTNlTdqec5RVcaGOeCKQ"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #44aa00; text-decoration: underline;"&gt;Michael Hanselmann&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt; - Trabalha para o Google Switzerland como Administrador de Sistemas, especificamente no desenvolvimento do projeto Ganeti. Ele mantem um projeto de hosting há 7 anos, participou no desenvolvimento do Gentoo por 5 anos e meio e contribuiu para diferentes projetos de Software Livre, incluindo o Linux Kernel. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="/articles/0044/1850/20120606-headshot.png" alt=""&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #44aa00;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://twitter.com/#%21/esplinr"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #44aa00; text-decoration: underline;"&gt;Richard Esplin&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt; – (EUA) Richard Esplin ajuda a construir comunidades de desenvolvedores em Alfresco, criando ferramentas para criar e compartilhar grandes trabalhos. Como defensor do software livre, ele se juntou à Alfresco para ver nascer uma empresa open source por dentro, aprendendo como o gerenciamento de conteúdo pode resolver muitos problemas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="/articles/0043/7459/gregorio.robles.lisboa.png" alt=""&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color: #00aa44;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="http://barba.libresoft.es:9673/webs/grex"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #00aa44;"&gt;Gregório Robles&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt; (Espanha) – Professor da Universidad Rey Juan Carlos, em Madri, Espanha. Seu trabalho de pesquisa é centrado no estudo do desenvolvimento de software livre pelo ponto de vista da engenharia. Desenvolveu e colaborou na concepção de programas para automatizar a análise de softwares livres e as ferramentas utilizada para produzi-los, como CVSAnalY.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="western" style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"&gt;&lt;img src="/articles/0043/7443/nelson.png" alt=""&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #00aa44;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.linkedin.com/pub/nelson-lago/31/104/53"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #00aa44; text-decoration: underline;"&gt;Nelson Lago&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt; - (Brasil) Gerente Técnico do Centro de Competência em Software Livre do IME/USP, onde trabalha pela divulgação do software livre, além de doutorando do Departamento de Ciência da Computação da Universidade de São Paulo. É graduado em música pela Escola de Comunicações e Artes da USP e mestre em ciência da computação pelo IME/USP. Participou do processo de criação da ONG LinuxSP. Atuou como administrador de sistemas em um dos primeiros provedores comerciais de acesso à Internet em São Paulo (That's Internet!), totalmente baseado em software livre.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;img src="/articles/0043/6958/bryant.png" alt=""&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color: #008000;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="http://twitter.com/debbryant"&gt;Deborah Bryant&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt; (USA) – Open source advocate since 1996 and collaborator at &lt;a href="http://osuosl.org/"&gt;osuosl.org&lt;/a&gt; for six years. Internationally known for her work on free software use incentive at the public sector, she currently is a consultant for governments worldwide in ICT (Information and Communication Technologies) adoption strategies. Bryant works in various non-profit boards in defense of open source, such as &lt;a href="http://opensource.org"&gt;opensource.org&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="http://osdv.org"&gt;osdv.org&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="http://codeforamerica.org"&gt;codeforamerica.org&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="/articles/0043/6960/anamatte.png" alt=""&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color: #008000;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="/acris/blog"&gt;Ana Cristina Fricke Matte&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt; (Brazil) - Teacher at &lt;a href="http://www.letras.ufmg.br/"&gt;FALE/UFMG&lt;/a&gt; and PhD in semiotics from &lt;a href="http://www.usp.br/"&gt;USP&lt;/a&gt;, she founded the group &lt;a href="http://www.textolivre.org/"&gt;Texto Livre&lt;/a&gt; (Free Text, in portuguese) in 2006, in which she has been working with Free Software from development to disclosure. Member of the &lt;a href="http://www.sleducacional.org/"&gt;SLEducacional&lt;/a&gt; since the begining of the group, interdisciplinar researcher in language and technology, coordinator of the lab &lt;a href="http://semiotec.textolivre.org/"&gt;SEMIOTEC&lt;/a&gt; and main editor of the scientific journal &lt;a href="http://www.periodicos.letras.ufmg.br/index.php/textolivre"&gt;Texto Livre: Linguagem e Tecnologia&lt;/a&gt;. With Texto Livre she organizes the events &lt;a href="http://gkosmos.com/evidosol"&gt;EVIDOSOL/CILTEC-online&lt;/a&gt; (Virtual Meeting on Free Software Documentation and International Congress of Online Language and Technology), &lt;a href="http://stis.lingtec.org/"&gt;STIS&lt;/a&gt; (SEMIOTEC Theoretical Interdisciplinar Seminars), &lt;a href="http://ueadsl.textolivre.pro.br/"&gt;UEADSL&lt;/a&gt; (University, Distant Learning and Free Software) and the Free Culture Day, an annual meeting at UFMG (Minas Gerais Federal University), and also runs the &lt;a href="http://www.portalprofessor.letras.ufmg.br/joomla"&gt;Portal do Professor Livre na Rede&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="/articles/0043/5053/daniela-feitosa.png" alt=""&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color: #008000;"&gt;&lt;a href="http://twitter.com/danifeitosa" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #008000;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Daniela Feitosa&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; (Brazil) - founding member of &lt;a href="http://colivre.coop.br/" target="_blank"&gt;Colivre&lt;/a&gt;, where she works as software developer and courses instructor, she currently is a release manager for &lt;a href="http://noosfero.org/" target="_blank"&gt;Noosfero&lt;/a&gt;, the Free Software platform for social networks (yes, the same one we use to run fisl!). Agile practices enthusiast, specifically Test Driven development and Pair Programming. PSL-BA collaborator, she has worked for the Bahia Free Software Festival and other community projects. She holds a Bachelors Degree in Computing Science from Bahia Federal University.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="/articles/0043/2961/amir-taaki.jpg" alt=""&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color: #008000;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="http://twitter.com/AmirTaaki" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #008000;"&gt;Amir Taak&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt; (England) - Game developer, Amir became known as the person behind Bitcoin Project. He´s been dedicating exclusively to free software development in the last 10 years.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="/articles/0043/2925/azevedo.jpg" alt=""&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color: #008000;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="http://twitter.com/ajazevedo" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #008000;"&gt;Alberto Azevedo&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt; (Brazil) - has a degree in IT by CEFET-PR, has more than 15 years of experience in IT, is a specialist in corporate networks security and security standards. He was general director at "Nova Era Informática e Telemática" and creator of the security methodology "ESP-h". Enthusiast and hacktivist in the Free Software Movement, he is the leader of the Project Security Experts Team and speaker in international events. Currently works as security advisor for large companies in Brazil.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;img src="/articles/0043/2967/aurelio.nadilson.1.jpg" alt=""&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color: #008000;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="http://identi.ca/aurium" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #008000;"&gt;Aurélio Heckert&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt; (Brazil) - Developer, digital graphics professional and Free Software Evangelist. Noosfero and Inkscape Team member, besides contributing to various other projects and users groups. He is a co-founder and contributor to PSL-BA, TWikiBrasil, Inkscape Brasil and COLIVRE - Cooperativa de Tecnologias Livres.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/a/a1/Seth_Schoen_EFF.jpg" height="168" alt="" width="221"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color: #008000;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.eff.org/about/staff/seth-schoen" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #008000;"&gt;Seth Schoen&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt; (USA) - Seth has been working for the &lt;a href="https://www.eff.org/" target="_blank"&gt;Electronic Frontier Foundation&lt;/a&gt; for more than 10 years and currently he is part of EFF´s senior tech staff. In these 10 years, he has contributed to the betterment of the public understanding of technology and their implications in the civil liberties. He helped create the live mini-distro  &lt;a href="http://www.lnx-bbc.com/" target="_blank"&gt;LNX-BBC&lt;/a&gt;, and researched events such as forensic tracking in printer codes, packet adulteration by internet providers (isp´s) and password recovery in ram memory with computers turned off.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="/articles/0043/2887/felix.png" alt=""&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color: #008000;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="/articles/0043/2210/randal-schwartz.png" alt=""&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;a href="http://twitter.com/merlyn" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Randal L. Schwartz&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (USA) - also known as the "Perl Magician", he is the co-author of various widely used books about that language. He also writes about Perl for regular columns in specialized tech magazines. Randal popularized the “Just another Perl hacker signature program”. He is a founding member of the Perl Mongers, the worldwide base organization for Perl defenders, and member of the Squeak Oversight Board, which supervises the Squeak programming language. He became a fisl fan, and is coming for the third time.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;img src="/articles/0043/2209/deivii.png" alt="Foto: Luciano Vargas"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;a href="http://identi.ca/deivi" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Deivi Lopes Kuhn&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (Brazil) - Economist, by the Universidade Federal do Rio Grande do Sul and post-graduate at the Universidade Federal de Lavras (MG) in Linux Network Administration. Deivi is an employee to SERPRO (the federal data processing organization) where he worked as a Local Network Admin, Development Projects Leader, Advisor to the Executive Board and Free Software Strategic Coordinator. Currently, he is Projects Coordinator at the Budget and Planning Secretary at the government of the Brazilian Federal District. Founding Associate to ASL and active member of the Brazilian Free Software community.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;img src="/articles/0043/2196/thomas.png" alt=""&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="http://twitter.com/ttsoares" target="_blank"&gt;Thomas Soares&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;(Brazil) - M&lt;span class="short_text"&gt;&lt;span class="hps"&gt;etallurgical engineer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; with a masters in Materials Science, he is a Free Software activist since 1994. Systems admin and network security researcher, currently he works for the Energy Revolution, developing research about the hidrpxy (HHO), electric motors (keppe) and energy generators (perendev, searl, bedini).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;img src="/articles/0042/3684/pedro-paranagua.jpg" alt=""&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.PedroParanagua.net" target="_blank"&gt;Pedro Paranaguá&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; (Brazil) -  professor, law and intellectual property public policies consultant, Internet and communication, has more than 10 years of national and international experience, has a master degree (cum laudae) in Intellectual Property, Internet and Policy from the University of London. Is a PhD student in the field of Intellectual Property, Internet and Policy in the &lt;a href="http://www.law.duke.edu/" target="_blank"&gt;Duke University&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000;"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;img src="/articles/0042/3651/dave-coffin.jpg" alt=""&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.cybercom.net/~dcoffin/" title="Site do Dave Coffin" target="_blank"&gt;Dave Coffin&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; (USA) - creator of &lt;a href="http://www.cybercom.net/~dcoffin/dcraw/index_pt.html" target="_blank"&gt;dcraw&lt;/a&gt;, a tool to develop raw image files from reflex cameras. Dcraw has become a standard, over its 15 years of activity, among GNU/Linux distros, and is also the basis in which other software build their compatibility with these kind of files. Because raw files from reflex cameras are preferred for advanced and professional photography, it can be said that dcraw bridges the gap for free software to work in this specific professional niche.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;img src="/articles/0042/3641/jbkempf.jpeg" alt=""&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.jbkempf.com/" target="_blank"&gt;Jean Baptiste Kempf&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; (France) - developer and musician, JB is the president of  &lt;a href="http://www.videolan.org/" target="_blank"&gt;VideoLan&lt;/a&gt;, a free software community that develops video projects - notably &lt;a href="http://www.videolan.org/vlc/" title="VLC" target="_blank"&gt;VLC&lt;/a&gt;, the popular open source multimedia player.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt; &lt;img src="/articles/0041/6851/gniibe.jpg" alt=""&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.gniibe.org/" target="_blank"&gt;Niibe Yukata&lt;/a&gt; (Japan) - &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;One of the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;founders&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;and current president of the &lt;a href="http://www.fsij.org/" target="_blank"&gt;Japan Free Software Initiative&lt;/a&gt;, Gniibe contributes to the GNU Project since 1989 and is a Debian Developer since 2005. He is also the main author of &lt;a href="http://www.fsij.org/gnuk/" target="_blank"&gt;Gnuk&lt;/a&gt;, a free software for criptography token implementation (OpenPGP) and of the &lt;a href="http://www.gniibe.org/memo/development/fst-01/fst-01-implementation" target="_blank"&gt;FST-01&lt;/a&gt;, a USB microcomputer.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;&lt;img src="/articles/0041/6854/psico-maddog.jpg" alt=""&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;&lt;a href="http://twitter.com/maddoghall" target="_blank"&gt;Jon Maddog Hall&lt;/a&gt; (USA)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt; - Founder and president of&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.li.org/" target="_blank"&gt;Linux Internacional&lt;/a&gt;, he has more than 40 years in the software industry. He devotes most of his time in free software events all over the world, and according to him, fisl is the largest community event in the planet. He is a confirmed presence every year, but not less interesting because of that, for the community, which, besides crowding his speeches, keeps taking many pictures by his side.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;img src="/articles/0041/6850/yorik-0.jpg" alt="" style="border-color: initial;"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://twitter.com/yorikvanhavre" target="_blank"&gt;Yorik Van Havre&lt;/a&gt; (Belgium/Brazil) - &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;Architect, freelance, designer and free software maniac, Yorik showcases with his portfolio that it is possible to work in graphic design (and architecture!) with free softwares. He is an active collaborator to the Blender and FreeCad communities, and share&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;s &lt;a href="http://yorik.uncreated.net/" target="_blank"&gt;tutorials, code, scripts, themes, models and others&lt;/a&gt; in Creative Commons for these softwares.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;img src="/articles/0041/6852/duda-nogueira.jpg" alt=""&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;&lt;a href="http://twitter.com/dudanogueira" target="_blank"&gt;Duda Nogueira&lt;/a&gt; (Brazil)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt; - communication professional &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;and Free Software enthusiast, Duda is an author of the &lt;a href="http://www.dudalibrary.org/" target="_blank"&gt;Duda Library&lt;/a&gt;, an effort from a community interested in building &lt;a href="http://rea.net.br/" target="_blank"&gt;open educational resources&lt;/a&gt;, thus contributing to the use of information and communication technologies in education.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;img src="/articles/0041/8829/marcelobranco.jpg" alt=""&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;a href="http://twitter.com/marcelobranco" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Marcel&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="http://twitter.com/marcelobranco" target="_blank"&gt;o Branco&lt;/a&gt; (Brazil)&lt;/strong&gt; - Former coordinator to the Associação Software Livre.org, he was one of the &lt;a href="http://conexoesglobais.com.br/" target="_blank"&gt;Conexões Globais 2.0&lt;/a&gt;'s creators. Marcelo was also the coordinator of the &lt;a href="http://dilmanarede.com.br/" target="_blank"&gt;social networks strategy&lt;/a&gt; to the candidate elect Dilma Rousseff, to the Presidency of Brazil. Three times general director of the &lt;a href="http://www.campus-party.com.br/" target="_blank"&gt;Campus Party Brasil&lt;/a&gt;, and worked to the spanish Generalitat de Catalunya government, as a counselor to the strategy for Free Software in the government. He is an evangelist and one of the founders of the Projeto Software Livre Brasil.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;img src="/articles/0041/8833/sergio-amadeu.png" height="218" alt="" width="218"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="http://twitter.com/samadeu" target="_blank"&gt;Sérgio Amadeu da Silveira&lt;/a&gt; (Brazil)&lt;/strong&gt; - &lt;span class="mw-redirect"&gt;sociologist&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;a href="http://www.trezentos.blog.br/" target="_blank"&gt;advocate and Free Software evangelist&lt;/a&gt; and also to Digital Inclusion in Brazil, he was one of the creators of the Telecentros Project in Latin America, and President of the National Institute of Information Technology. Sérgio holds a PhD in Political Science from the São Paulo University, and currently is an associate professor to the ABC Federal University (&lt;a href="http://www.ufabc.edu.br/" target="_blank"&gt;UFABC&lt;/a&gt;), where he co-leads a research group &lt;a href="http://www.ufabcdigital.blog.br/" target="_blank"&gt;Digital Culture and Sharing Networks&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;img src="/articles/0041/8834/paulo2.jpg" height="218" alt="" width="218"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="http://twitter.com/paulormm" target="_blank"&gt;Paulo Meirelles&lt;/a&gt; - (Brazil) -&lt;/strong&gt; PhD student in the Computing Science Department from São Paulo University. Since 2004 he is a member of the group  “&lt;a href="/paulormm" target="_blank"&gt;Project Software Livre Rio Grande do Norte&lt;/a&gt;” (PSL-RN), where he collaborates in free software popularization both in its social, tech and legal aspects. He is an associate to the NGO “Associação Software Livre” (ASL.org) since 2006. He contributes to three free software projects: &lt;a href="http://ccsl.ime.usp.br/redmine/projects/analizo" target="_blank"&gt;Analizo&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="/mezuro/kalibro/about" target="_blank"&gt;Kalibro&lt;/a&gt; e &lt;a href="http://ccsl.ime.usp.br/wiki/index.php/MezuroXP2012" target="_blank"&gt;Mezuro&lt;/a&gt;. Has articles published in both national and international conferences and gave courses and speeches in many national free software events.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;img src="/articles/0041/8835/bruno-souza.jpg" height="218" alt="" width="218"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bruno Souza - (Brazil) -&lt;/strong&gt; founder and leader of the SouJava, elected for the JCP's Executive Committee in May. That's the most important committee for the definition of standards to the Java technology. From 2007 to 2009 Bruno was a conselor to the Open Source Initiative administration, where he currently holds an Emeritus status.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 13 Apr 2012 20:45:59 +0000</pubDate><link>http://softwarelivre.org/fisl13/guest-speakers</link><guid>http://softwarelivre.org/fisl13/guest-speakers</guid></item></channel></rss>